festival.introText:
RELOAD FESTIVAL - UKG IN THE FOREST

July brings the biggest UKG line-up around straight to the Forest!!

For one day only, deep in Nottingham’s Lime Lane Woods, Reload Festival 2023 will be popping off with the hottest UKG artists and DJs for a crazy, up-for-it audience. Will you be in the crowd? 

Nothing beats a forest festival. Escaping the hustle and bustle of the city to immerse yourself in the deep bass, shuffling drums, and soft vocals of UKG with others who also want to let go and feel the music is an unbeatable experience. And it’s finally coming to Nottingham.

Reload Festival will be bringing the biggest UKG line-up around straight to Thoresby Park. Hosted across 2 stages again, expect BIGGER production, HUGE lineup + an insane VIP area for that extra special rave experience

This is one you don't want to miss out on

It’s about time! If letting loose in a forest to your favourite jams sounds right up your street, grab your Reload Festival tickets now to avoid disappointment.

faqs.question: When is Reload Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Reload Festival will take place on Saturday 5th August 2023.

faqs.question: How to get to reload festival?
faqs.answer:
you can get to reload festival by train, bus or car. these are the lines and routes that have stops nearby:

Nearest station: Hucknall (4.6km)

Nearest Bus stops: Mansfield road (N)

Nearby roads B684

faqs.question: Is there camping at Reload Fest?
faqs.answer: No , there is not camping at Reload Fest as it is a one day event.

faqs.question: Is there disabled access at Reload Festival?
faqs.answer: Yes, the Festival is on a flat field, with disabled toilets.

faqs.question: How much are Reload Festival tickets?
faqs.answer: Head to the tickets section to find out the latest ticket prices.

faqs.question: Where is Reload Festival?
faqs.answer: Reload Festival is located in Thoresby Park in Nottingham.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Payment plan tickets are currently not on sale.

faqs.question: Is there an age restriction at Reload Festival?
faqs.answer: Yes there is , you will need to be 18 or older. Reload operate a challenge-21 policy upon Entry and at All Bars, if you look younger than 21, bring ID.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.
